cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with hyperspectral image classification using convolutional neural networks. The paper also proposes a novel architecture that encodes spectral contextual information and uses graph attention mechanism for interpretable reasoning in the spatial domain, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with high-dimensional data and limited labelled data, which may also make it relevant to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
